Source:  Through the Looking Glass
Author:  MEIKLE
Vol / Page:  125
Edition:
Quote:  My brothers' slang and `funny' sayings delighted me. ... I remember [126] such words as `batty', `hoot' and `spondulicks' and many that ... were corruptions of Maori words. I spell them here as they sounded to me then: <i>ehoa, harka, kupai, kure, munga munga typo, markuta, pooku, tangy. </i>
